The dataset contains the following information:
1、 	 Zircon U-Pb age and trace element spectrum data produced by third-party detection;
2、 	 Sr-nd-pb-hf-s-pb-h-o isotopic geochemical data of whole rock and single mineral produced by third-party detection;
3、 	 RB Sr and SM Nd isotopic data generated by third-party detection;
4、 	 Data of major and trace elements such as pyrite, pyrrhotite and chlorite produced by third-party detection;
5、 	 Trace elements and micro temperature measurement data of fluid inclusions produced by third-party detection;
6、 	 In situ major and trace element data of minerals produced by third-party detection;
7、 	 Geochemical data of rocks and ores generated through third-party detection;
8、 	 40Ar / 39Ar data of mica produced by third-party detection;
9、 	 Alteration structure mapping data of key mining areas in Tibet obtained from field geological survey of the project team;
10. The field measured broadband seismic observation data, short period dense array observation data and extracted receiver function data of the project team;
The above data are collected in Tibet and Yunnan. Mainly in the Institute of mineral resources, Chinese Academy of Geological Sciences, Institute of geochemistry, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Institute of Geology and Geophysics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Institute of analysis and testing, Beijing Geological Research Institute of nuclear industry, Peking University, Nanjing University, laboratory of School of resources and environmental engineering, Hefei University of technology, Wuhan Shangpu laboratory State Key Laboratory of mineral deposit research, Nanjing University, State Key Laboratory of isotope geochemistry, Guangzhou Institute of geochemistry, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Key Laboratory of minerals and metallogeny, China University of Geosciences (Beijing), China University of Geosciences (Wuhan), National Geological Experiment and testing center, Aoshi analysis and testing Guangzhou Co., Ltd., Beijing Kehui Testing Technology Co., Ltd The noble gas Laboratory of Pacific isotope and geochemistry research center of Columbia University, Queen's isotope research center of Queen's University and microanalysis Laboratory of Memorial University of Canada completed the test and analysis. The instruments used include Agilent 7500a-icp-ms instrument, Redmond photon machines analyzer G2 laser ablation multi receiver inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometer, RIGAKU Rix 2000 spectrometer X-fluorescence spectrometer, jeol jxa-8100 electron probe, Shimadzu sequential 1800 spectrometer X-fluorescence spectrometer, obitraq fusion high throughput mass spectrometer sequencer, jeol JCXA-733 electron probe Finnigan Triton thermal ionization mass spectrometer, Argus VI inert gas mass spectrometer, Horiba xplora plus micro confocal laser Raman spectrometer, cameca ims-1280 secondary ion mass spectrometer (SIMS), gv-5400 mass spectrometer, jeol880m electron probe, RIGAKU Rix 2000 spectrometer X fluorescence spectrometer, nu plasma II MC-ICP-MS, Zeiss V16, V20 stereo microscope, scanning electron microscope Compexpro 102 ARF 193nm excimer laser and microlas optical system composition, wsp-1 spectrometer, analyze he instrument of photon machine company, compex102f 193nm excimer laser, Axios pw4400 X-ray fluorescence spectrometer, Perkin Elmer ICP-MS instrument, Finnigan mat ‐ 262 thermal ionization mass spectrometer (TIMS), element-2 mass spectrometer, jeol-jxa-8230m electron probe Tjax series ICP-MS, multi receiver inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometry (MC-ICPMS), etc. The collection time is 2018-2021.
